<div class="blurb">
	<h1>Alexis Langlois-Rémillard</h1>
	<h2>Ph.D. student at Universiteit Gent</h2>
	<hr> 
		<p> 
			Since April 2019, I am working at Universiteit Gent in the broad topic of representation 
			theory of algebras with a focus on symmetry algebra of Dirac-like operators and applications to mathematical physics. My supervisors are
			Joris Van der Jeugt and Hendrik De Bie.
		</p>
		<p>			
			I did my bachelor and master degrees at Université de Montréal, the latter under the direction of Yvan Saint-Aubin
			on the representation theory of seam algebras, a generalization of Temperley-Lieb algebras.
		</p>
		
		<p>
			I am in my last year of PhD and should defend in the Spring 2023. From May to September 2023, I should 
			be working with Érika Roldán-Roa in Leipzig.
		</p>
		
		<p>
		In October 2023, I will begin a Hausdorff postdoc at the Hausdorff Center in Mathematics in Bonn
		</p>
	
	
	<h3>Where will I be in the near future?</h3>
	<p>
		I will stay in Ghent until May (with possibly some vacations). Make sure to come to our mini-course on p-Kazhdan-Lusztig combinatorics 17-21 April!	
	</p>
	
	<p>
	My next big travel for conference will be to Okinawa June 05-10	<a href="https://groups.oist.jp/hecke-algebras-and-categorification">Representation theory of Hecke algebras and categorification</a>
	</p>
	
		
	
	<h3>Research interests </h3>
		<p> 
			I am interested in rational Cherednik algebras, reflection groups, Dunkl operators, Dirac-like operators and (deformations of) Lie (super)algebras. 
			I approach these subjects via representation theory. I also enjoy a lot diagrammatic algebras and categories, and diagrammatic calculus.
			
			I have also recently been interested in complexity theory and extremal combinatorics through chess-inspired mathematical problems.
			 <!--I try to give an overview of my articles in my <a href="/research_notes/">research notes</a>-->
		</p>
